article.description: — Elijah Hutchins-Everett picked up a loose ball in the key and scored with 2.3 seconds left to lift Austin Peay to a 69-67 win over Howard on Friday.
article.headline: Hutchins-Everett carries Austin Peay over Howard 69-67
article.linkText: Hutchins-Everett carries Austin Peay over Howard 69-67
article.story: WASHINGTON -- — Elijah Hutchins-Everett picked up a loose ball in the key and scored with 2.3 seconds left to lift Austin Peay to a 69-67 win over Howard on Friday. The Governors were going for a last shot but as the play initiated, the phone guard lost the handle as he drove past the foul line. Hutchins-Everett dug out the loose ball, spun and laid it it. Hutchins-Everett had 14 points and 10 rebounds and Cameron Copeland had 16 points and seven steals for Austin Peay (3-2). Tariq Silver added 14 points. Caleb Stone-Carrawell had 10 points and six assists. Tai Bibbs had 12 points for the Bison (4-3). Kyle Foster added 12 points. Elijah Hawkins had 11 points and five steals. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
